<statement>
<p>Which of the following is largest amount (rather than largest percent)? </p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>94<percent/> of 63</li> 
<li>24<percent/> of 183</li> 
<li>4<percent/> of 1731</li> 
</ol></p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>C: 4<percent/> of 1731</li></ul></p><p>We must first calculate (or at least approximate) each value.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{94}\%\cdot{63}={59.22}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{24}\%\cdot{183}={43.92}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{4}\%\cdot{1731}={69.24}</m></p>
<p>From these calculations we see that 4<percent/> of 1731 is the largest.</p>

</solution>
